focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Grammar and Usage</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Part of speech</strong>: Verb</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Verb forms</strong>: moralize – moralized – moralizing</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Transitive/Intransitive</strong>: Both</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Intransitive: \"He tends to moralize when giving speeches.\"</li>\n<li>Transitive: \"The author moralizes the tale by emphasizing honesty.\"</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"sentence-patterns\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#sentence-patterns\" aria-label=\"sentence patterns permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Sentence patterns</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>moralize about + topic</strong> → \"The teacher moralized about responsibility.\"</li>\n<li><strong>moralize on/upon + topic</strong> → \"She moralized upon the dangers of greed.\"</li>\n<li><strong>moralize story/incident</strong> → \"Writers often moralize their stories.\"</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"common-phrases\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#common-phrases\" aria-label=\"common phrases permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Common Phrases</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>moralize about something</strong></li>\n<li><strong>moralize on/upon something</strong></li>\n<li><strong>moralize a tale</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"collocations\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#collocations\" aria-label=\"collocations permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Collocations</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>moralize endlessly</strong></li>\n<li><strong>moralize heavily</strong></li>\n<li><strong>tendency to moralize</strong></li>\n<li><strong>moralize a story/parable</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"examples\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#examples\" aria-label=\"examples permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Examples</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>The politician began to moralize about family values.</li>\n<li>He doesn’t just teach; he tends to moralize, which puts off his students.</li>\n<li>The book moralizes the dangers of envy and greed.</li>\n<li>Rather than moralizing about mistakes, she offered practical advice.</li>\n<li>Parents often moralize to their children about honesty.</li>\n<li>The preacher moralized on the importance of forgiveness.</li>\n<li>Critics said the film moralized too much instead of letting the story speak for itself.</li>\n<li>He tried not to moralize when his friend confessed the mistake.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"synonyms-or-related\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#synonyms-or-related\" aria-label=\"synonyms or related permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Synonyms or Related</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>preach</li>\n<li>lecture</li>\n<li>sermonize</li>\n<li>pontificate</li>\n<li>advise</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"antonym\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#antonym\" aria-label=\"antonym permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Antonym</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>ignore</li>\n<li>overlook</li>\n<li>condone</li>\n<li>accept without judgment</li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"moralize meaning and examples","date":"2025-09-06","description":"English learning materials; moralize explanation.","tags":["English","verb"],"featuredImage":{"publicURL":"/static/640801cee3fa47ba44d58cca3779b40e/moralize.png","childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","backgroundColor":"#f8e8b8","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/640801cee3fa47ba44d58cca3779b40e/b5658/moralize.png","srcSet":"/static/640801cee3fa47ba44d58cca3779b40e/acb7c/moralize.png 256w,\n/static/640801cee3fa47ba44d58cca3779b40e/ccc41/moralize.png 512w,\n/static/640801cee3fa47ba44d58cca3779b40e/b5658/moralize.png 1024w","sizes":"(min-width: 1024px) 1024px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/640801cee3fa47ba44d58cca3779b40e/22bfc/moralize.webp 256w,\n/static/640801cee3fa47ba44d58cca3779b40e/d689f/moralize.webp 512w,\n/static/640801cee3fa47ba44d58cca3779b40e/67ded/moralize.webp 1024w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 1024px) 1024px, 100vw"}]},"width":1024,"height":1024}}}}},"relatedPosts":{"nodes":[]},"previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/predicament/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"predicament meaning and examples"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/praise/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"praise meaning and examples"}}},"pageContext":{"id":"0a3c1c5c-64df-547f-98d1-9077794d8c57","previousPostId":"b4a969cc-5511-54ea-a32a-08e04dfec495","nextPostId":"0bea11a9-b0ca-5cc0-a52e-c3f6cddef83e","relatedPosts":[]}},"staticQueryHashes":["2841359383"],"slicesMap":{}}